flowRoot.flowPara: Assault of a Federal Officer (Two Counts); Negligent Manslaughter with a Parahuman Power (Two Counts); Arson (Twelve Counts); Assault with a Parahuman Power (Five Counts); Impersonation of a Federal Officer; Destruction of Federal Property; Possession of a Schedule II Controlled Substance; Conspiracy; Shoplifting (Fifty-Seven Counts); Operation of an Unregistered Trailer or Motor Vehicle; Harboring a Fugitive; Tax Evasion;
The Parahuman Response Team is offering a reward of up to $5,000 for information leading to the arrest and conviction of "Misfit Maid" or her known cohort "Blur".

"Misfit Maid" and her cohort, "Blur", are known to reside in the Devilfish, MN area. They also have ties to Ashton, Washington, and the Idaho Panhandle region. Both individuals are known to have Parahuman powers. "Misfit Maid" is a shapeshifter and can turn into a chimera-like creature, and "Blur" is known to manipulate light and create stealth technology.

"Misfit Maid" was most recently seen escaping PRT custody after maiming a child Ward and damaging federal government property. "Blur" was last seen in the area of the Douglass A. Fender Federal Building and U.S. Courthouse after responding to an S-class call for help under the Endbringer Defense Act of 1994.

flowPara.flowSpan: SHOULD BE CONSIDERED ARMED AND DANGEROUS

flowRoot.flowPara: If you have any information concerning this case, please contact the PRT's Toll-Free Tipline at 1-800-PRT-TIPS (1-800-778-8477). You may also contact your local FBI office, the nearest police station, or you can submit a tip online at tips.prt.gov.
Field Office: Devilfish / Ashton Case No.: BOI-2017-1246

"Misfit Maid" is wanted for involvement in a string of assaults, arsons, and other crimes against innocent civilians. She has repeatedly shown no hesitation in maiming others for their religious or political beliefs. Her cohort "Blur" has willingly aided and abetted these crimes and will no doubt continue doing so.
